title: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) which are showing up prominently in the Open Type dialog.
OB: The Open Type dialog prominently displays obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) from JDK 1.4.
EB: Obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) should be displayed with less prominence in the Open Type dialog.
SR:
To reproduce:
1. Launch the software and navigate to the Open Type dialog.\n2. Observe the presence of obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) from JDK 1.4.
